From 52950a1fc5835dfcdf1b46d4bacb38f34d9a0678 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Luis Diego Rodriguez <ldrodriguezr@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 03:56:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: realtime, markdown, keyboard shortcuts, dynamic tags,
 burndown chart

P1 - Real-time Supabase subscriptions
- useRealtimeIssues hook: auto-refresh Board & Backlog on any issue change
- No more manual load() polling needed

P1 - Markdown in descriptions
- react-markdown added (+ recharts for burndown)
- IssueModal: Edit/Preview toggle with syntax-highlighted preview
- Textarea uses monospace font in edit mode

P1 - Keyboard shortcuts
- useKeyboardShortcuts hook (skips shortcuts when typing in inputs)
- C = create issue, / = focus search, Esc = close modal
- Shortcut hint shown in search placeholder and Create button
- ? button in Board toolbar opens shortcuts reference modal

P2 - Dynamic project tags (replaces hardcoded TAGS constant)
- Migration 003: jira.project_tags table with RLS
- db.ts: getProjectTags, createProjectTag, deleteProjectTag
- AppContext: projectTags[] and refreshTags() available globally
- ProjectsPage: Tags button per project opens add/delete manager
- IssueModal + BoardPage create form use dynamic tags from context

P2 - Burndown chart in Dashboard
- getBurndownData() in db.ts (uses updated_at as done-date proxy)
- recharts LineChart: actual remaining vs ideal line
- Sprint selector dropdown; auto-selects active sprint on load
